Topic:: Explain Justice as fairness. How does an overlapping consensus among cultural, religious, and ideological group is achieved by Rawls
Date:: 2022-11-22
Course:: [[UPSC/PSIR\|PSIR]] 

----
>[!error]  Introduction 
>Rawl's theorem of justice was mainly worried about outcome of liberal theorem of justice. And he completely rejected the methodology of Marxist and socialist justice. He was willing to fuse procedural and substantive justice. He saw justice as fairness. 


> [!done] Body 
>  Explain what is fairness in Rawl's theory of justice. 
>  
>  How he bring consensus among everyone. 
>  - By bringing this fairness he imagines Original Position. 
>  

For Rawl's justice as fairness in society is his idea of justice in liberal society. He conceived his idea in his book, 'Theory of Justice'.  He talked about justice as fairness where men were free and equal and society was fair. It was his way of resolving the debate between equality and freedom. 

> Justice as fairness aims to describe a just arrangement of the major political and social institution of liberal society. 

He wanted to describe a just arrangement of political and social institution by presenting justice as fairness. He also included family, political, constitutional, legal system and economy to describe his conception of justice.

This arrangement he calls as basic structure. It was the location of justice because these institution distribute main burden and benefit of social life. 

To bring about his theorem of justice he imagined a condition that is *original position*. Where he aims to move from abstract conception to determinate principals of social justice.  

The original position is a situation where each citizen is free and equal. Where everyone wants what an equal and free person wants. And all agrees to basic structure while situated fairly with respect to each other.

Original Position brings in 'vigil of ignorance' which prevents unnecessary facts which can influence agreement among their citizens. 

Each person of original position therefore is deprived of knowing race, class, religion, ethnicity, race, gender and wealth of citizens they represent. These are all such facts which are irrelevant to choice of principle of justice. 

Parties do know that citizen in society have different comprehensive doctrine and plans of life. The society is under condition of moderate scarcity, there is enough to go around, but not enough for everyone for what they want. 




>[!todo] Conclusion
>Raw's theory of justice and his conception of Original position and vigil of ignorance situates very diverse people fairly with respect to each other. Each citizen is free and equal, and is treated fairly by society.
